  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from an app like **AppLock** (or any similar app) can be challenging, especially if the photos were deleted directly from the app or its secured storage. However, here are some steps you can try to recover your deleted photos:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Check the AppLock Backup Folder**\n- Some versions of AppLock create a backup folder where locked photos might still be stored.\n- Use a file manager app (like **Files by Google** or **ES File Explorer**) and navigate to:\n  ```\n  Internal Storage/AppLock/\n  ```\n  or\n  ```\n  Internal Storage/DCIM/.AppLock/\n  ```\n  Look for a folder named \"Backup\" or \"Hidden\" to see if your photos are still there.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Check the Recycle Bin (if available)**\n- If AppLock has a recycle bin or trash feature, open the app and check if your deleted photos are still in the bin. You may be able to restore them from there.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Use a Data Recovery App**\n- If the photos are deleted from the app and the phone\u2019s storage, you can use a data recovery app to scan your device for deleted files. Some popular apps include:\n  - **DiskDigger**\n  - **PhotoRec**\n  - **EaseUS MobiSaver**\n- To use these apps:\n  1. Install the recovery app from the Google Play Store.\n  2. Grant the necessary permissions.\n  3. Scan your device\u2019s internal storage for deleted photos.\n  4. Recover the photos to a safe location.\n\n**Note:** Act quickly, as new data being written to your phone can overwrite the deleted photos.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Check Cloud Backups**\n- If you have enabled cloud backups (e.g., Google Photos, Google Drive, or OneDrive), check if the deleted photos are still available in the trash or backup folder of the cloud service.\n- Open the respective app, go to the \"Trash\" or \"Bin\" section, and restore the photos if they are there.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Contact AppLock Support**\n- If none of the above methods work, you can reach out to the **AppLock support team**:\n  - Open the AppLock app.\n  - Go to \"Settings\" or \"Help.\"\n  - Look for the \"Contact Us\" or \"Support\" option.\n  - Explain your issue and ask if they can assist in recovering your photos.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Prevent Future Data Loss**\n- Enable backups for your photos (e.g., Google Photos or other cloud services).\nYou can also use external storage (e.g., USB drives or SD cards) to back up important data regularly.\n\n---\n\nIf the photos were extremely important and none of the above methods work, you may need to consult a professional data recovery service, though this can be expensive. Always act quickly to maximize the chances of recovery!",
